---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/paths';

// Public terms of use for a self-led, free-account course (MVP — no payments).
const updated = 'June 12, 2026';
const contactEmail = 'hello@thoughtfuldesign.io';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — Thoughtful Design"
  description="The terms for using the Thoughtful Design self-led course."
>
  <article class="container legal">
    <header class="legal__head">
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose legal__body">
      <p>
        These terms cover your use of Thoughtful Design (the “course”). By creating an account,
        you agree to them. If you do not agree, please don't create an account.
      </p>

      <h2>Your account</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You must be at least 18 years old to enroll.</li>
        <li>You're responsible for keeping your sign-in details secure and for activity under your account.</li>
        <li>One account is for one person. Please don't share account credentials.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How the course works</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The course is self-led and asynchronous. There are no live sessions, deadlines, or cohorts.</li>
        <li>One preview lesson per module is open to everyone. The full course unlocks when you enroll.</li>
        <li>
          Module, milestone, and final assessments are scored. You need 80% to pass each one, and you
          can retry as many times as you need. A certificate is issued automatically once you pass
          every required assessment.
        </li>
        <li>
          We may update, add, or revise lessons, assessments, and resources to improve the course over time.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Using the content</h2>
      <p>
        The lessons, assessments, and framework templates are provided for your own professional
        learning and practice. You may use the framework templates in your own work. Please don't
        resell, republish, or redistribute the course content as your own.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        Don't attempt to break, scrape, overload, or gain unauthorized access to the platform or
        to other learners' data. We may suspend accounts that do.
      </p>

      <h2>Cancellation</h2>
      <p>
        You can delete your account at any time from your
        <a href={withBase('/account')}>account settings</a>. There is nothing to cancel or unsubscribe
        from — this version of the course is free and does not bill you.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        The course is provided “as is.” It offers professional education and judgment, not guaranteed
        outcomes. You're responsible for how you apply what you learn in your own work.
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our <a href={withBase('/privacy')}>Privacy Policy</a> explains what we collect and how to
        delete it. It's part of these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Email <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding: 2.5rem 0 3.5rem;
    max-width: var(--content-width);
  }

  .legal__head {
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal__head h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
  }

  .legal__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
  }
</style>
